<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO-CHOICE GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * On Mother's Day, The Times chose to print an opinion piece by an abortion 
advocate (Column Left, May 8).No surprise there. But, by continuing to identify 
Frances Kissling's so-called "Catholics for a Free Choice" without 
qualification or disclaimer, The Times is in complicity with a fraud. As the 
U.S. Catholic bishops recently stated, "Many people may be led to believe that 
it is an authentic Catholic organization. It is not. It has no affiliation, 
formal or otherwise, with the Catholic Church," and "merits no recognition or 
support as a Catholic organization." 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN PAUL ARNERICH 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
