<HEADLINE>
<P>
WHAT'S THE DEAL?: CLEAR CORRECTIONS FOR THE NEARSIGHTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When nearsightedness is the problem, there are plenty of routes to clearer 
vision: 
</P>
<P>
 * New Vue cosmetically tinted, disposable contact lenses, a six-pack (lenses 
only) from For Eyes Optical, Los Angeles area stores, $39. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jimmy Jack-style lightweight plastic single vision lens with 10-layer 
anti-reflective, scratch-resistant coating at LA Eyeworks, $245. 
</P>
<P>
 * Squinting over 20 years, producing enough wrinkles to warrant a deep 
chemical peel around the eye area, $1,500. 
</P>
<P>
 * Laser corneal reshaping surgery (also called photo-refractive keratectomy or 
PRK) at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, $2,000 per eye. KATHLEEN DOHENY 
</P>
