<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: MANHATTAN BEACH; MAN 
HELD FOR QUESTIONING ABOUT MURDER OF OFFICER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Immigration agents Monday arrested a deportee in Virginia who Los Angeles 
detectives want to question about the murder of Manhattan Beach police officer. 
 
</P>
<P>
 The 25-year-old man "is not considered a suspect" in the Dec. 27 killing of 
Martin Ganz, but "he has similar features described in the composite (drawing 
of the killer) and in one of the clues received by the task force" of 
investigators, said George Ducoulombier, a Los Angeles County Sheriff's 
Department spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The task force investigating the crime has received more than 1,800 tips, 
Ducoulombier said. 
</P>
<P>
 The man was arrested on a no-bail warrant from California for failing to leave 
the country, Ducoulombier said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ganz's killer is described as an Asian, possibly Filipino, age 25 to 39, and 
possibly 5 feet, 6 inches to 5 feet, 10 inches tall with a medium build. 
</P>
