<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP PLAYOFFS AT A GLANCE; CITY SECTION GIRLS SOFTBALL FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Today's pairings (at UCLA): Division 4-A -- Woodland Hills El Camino vs. San 
Pedro, 5 p.m.: Division 3-A -- Tujunga Verdugo Hills vs.Sepulveda Monroe, 3 
p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's champions: Division 4-A -- San Pedro; 3-A -- Verdugo Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Outlook: Top-seeded San Pedro (20-4) is playing for a third consecutive 4-A 
title, having defeated Wilmington Banning in the title game last year, 7-0. San 
Pedro is led by pitcher Petrina Martinez, who threw a three-hit, 2-0 shutout 
against Chatsworth in the semifinals last week. Martinez and shortstop Victoria 
Brucker were the 1993 4-A co-players of the year. El Camino Real (19-4) also 
has strong pitching. Jennifer Gould recorded 12 strikeouts and allowed only 
four hits in a 7-0 semifinal victory over Sylmar. In 3-A, Verdugo Hills (18-3) 
didn't lose much after last year's starter, Rachel Maldonado, left the team 
early in the season. Verdugo Hills' new starting pitcher, Schannon Schoonover, 
is 15-0 since replacing Maldonado. First baseman Maryanne May is Verdugo Hills' 
most productive offensive player. She led the Northern League in home runs with 
nine. Monroe (16-2) committed six errors in its semifinal game against 
Westchester but still won, 12-2, after receiving multiple hits from five 
players. GREG SANDOVAL 
</P>
