<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: LONDON; ANTI-NAZIS TO RALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Britain's Anti-Nazi League will hold a Carnival Against the Nazis in South 
London on Saturday to highlight what it calls an alarming rise of the political 
far-right in Europe.Rock bands will provide an enticement to newcomers. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anti-Nazi League was revived in 1992 when its adherents, including many 
members of Parliament, saw the emerging strength of neo-fascist parties in 
Europe. Many of these parties are running candidates in the June 9 election to 
the European Parliament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
