<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; WOMAN, 18, HIT BY GAS TANKER DIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An 18-year-old woman who ran from behind a bus into the path of a gas tanker 
died Sunday from her injuries, authorities said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Brandi Adams, who lived at the El Toro Marine Corps Air Station, died at 5:30 
p.m. at Western Medical Center-Santa Ana, California Highway Patrol Officer 
Angel Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson said Adams got off an Orange County Transit Authority bus on C Street 
just west of 9th Street on the marine base about 1:15 p.m. Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 She then ran into the street behind the bus and was struck by the gas tanker, 
which was moving eastbound on C at about 25 m.p.h. The driver, Dennis P. 
Sobanski, 41, of Long Beach, was not cited, Johnson said.LYNN FRANEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
