<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; DEADLINE FOR FAIR ENTRIES IS WEDNESDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All competitive entries for the Orange County Fair must be at the fairground 
office by 4 p.m. Wednesday, and postmarked entries that arrive later will not 
be considered. 
</P>
<P>
 More than 23,000 people entered photography, livestock, floral arrangements, 
visual art and other work in hundreds of contests, fairground spokeswoman Judy 
Barnes said. 
</P>
<P>
 Cash awards, trophies and ribbons are given as prizes, and most work is 
displayed during the 17-day July fair. 
</P>
<P>
 People may compete in amateur, novice and professional categories. There are 
separate competitions for adults and children. 
</P>
<P>
 All together, there are more than 5,000 separate contests, Barnes said. The 
fair received more than 39,000 entries in 1993, Barnes said. 
</P>
<P>
 Entry forms are available at the fairgrounds, 88 Fair Drive, Costa Mesa. 
Completed forms must be returned there. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 708-1553.WILLSON CUMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
