<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MAN PLEADS INSANITY IN WOMAN'S SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 25-year-old man pleaded not guilty by reason of insanity in connection with 
the Mother's Day slaying of an Oxnard woman who was his former girlfriend. 
</P>
<P>
 Gary Michael Rose, who neighbors say moved to Oxnard just several weeks before 
the May 8 shooting, faces one count of murder with use of a firearm.He is being 
held at Ventura County Jail in lieu of a $250,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 Neither Deputy Public Defender Douglas W. Daily nor Deputy Dist. Atty. Donald 
C. Glynn could be immediately reached for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Police say that Rose shot 31-year-old Victoria Ramey in her La Canada Avenue 
home about 9:30 p.m. He called police to the scene after the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
 Friends of the victim say Rose moved to the area from Indiana and was staying 
with Ramey until he could find a job. Ramey, who neighbors said liked to help 
people, had been engaged to the defendant several years ago, friends said. 
DWAYNE BRAY 
</P>
</TEXT>
