<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CALABASAS; CITY SEEKS TO ANNEX GATED COMMUNITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KURT PITZER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At the request of homeowners, the Calabasas City Council has proposed annexing 
a gated community that abuts land slated for the massive Ahmanson Ranch project 
in Ventura County's Simi Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 Annexing the 825-acre Mountain View Estates would give Calabasas control over 
a larger section of the Los Angeles County portion of Thousand Oaks Boulevard 
-- a proposed access to Ahmanson Ranch -- but would not block plans for the 
mini-city, said Calabasas Planning Director Steve Harris. 
</P>
<P>
 Calabasas must get permission to annex the land from the Los Angeles County 
Local Agency Formation Commission, which oversees boundary changes. Calabasas 
sent its application to the commission this month, Harris said, but the review 
process often takes as long as a year.  
</P>
<P>
 The application was filed after 49 residents of the area north of the Ventura 
Freeway between the city line and Crummer Canyon Road petitioned Calabasas 
officials, saying they wanted to enjoy the benefits of living in the city. The 
area includes Gates Canyon Park. KURT PITZER 
</P>
</TEXT>
