<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIGHT THE OJAI TOWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Did you know that the people of Ojai, Oak View, Meiners Oaks, Casitas Springs, 
Santa Paula and north Ventura are being exposed to radiation daily? 
</P>
<P>
 Thousands of men, women, children and family pets are being exposed daily to 
unnecessary radiation.Thanks to our government. 
</P>
<P>
 Over Thanksgiving weekend, the National Weather Service erected a very 
powerful microwave radiation tower in a populated area of Ojai. The government 
admits that the tower's radiation can be harmful. It didn't stop them -- it was 
built anyway. 
</P>
<P>
 There was no environmental impact study, there was no local notification and 
the federal government condemned land that belonged to an 86-year-old woman. 
This was done because of a court ruling that prevented the federal government 
from illegally using a private road to build this massive microwave transmitter 
tower. They wanted the land, so they seized it. 
</P>
<P>
 We all must fight this. This tower may not be in your neighborhood or mine, 
but we must show the government that we will not sit by and let them expose 
innocent people to radiation. 
</P>
<P>
 We must let them know that we want this tower moved to a more remote and 
suitable area, far enough away from residents so that there would be no health 
risks. 
</P>
<P>
 We must not cover our eyes. This could be in our neighborhood. We must all get 
involved. 
</P>
<P>
 Please write to Rep. (Elton) Gallegly, Sen. (Dianne) Feinstein, Sen. (Barbara) 
Boxer. We must support our neighbors in the Ojai area and let the government 
know that we will not sit back and let them do this to our neighbors. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, contact CARE (Citizens Against Radiation Exposure) at 
656-6656. 
</P>
<P>
 DEBRA NINNEMAN BURKE 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park 
</P>
