<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Courtney Pugmire 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Track / Distance 
</P>
<P>
 Pugmire pulled off an impressive double by winning the 1,600 and 800 meters at 
the Southern Section Division II championships, helping her team to the title 
Saturday.Pugmire is an 800 specialist who has run the 1,600 about five times in 
competition, but she out-kicked more experienced runners to win in 5 minutes 
6.62 seconds. In the 800, Pugmire again was challenged late in the race and 
held on for the victory in 2:16.64. "Both times when she was challenged, if she 
had it, she answered and came back," Esperanza Coach Al Britt said. Other 
notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Stephanie Bernritter, Woodbridge, pitched a one-hitter in a 5-2 Division III 
victory over Trabuco Hills. 
</P>
<P>
