<HEADLINE>
<P>
THREE SIGN TO PLAY BASKETBALL FOR TITANS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton has received letters of intent from two community college 
basketball players and one high school player. 
</P>
<P>
 The two community college players are Ali Nayab, a 5-9 point guard from 
Southwestern College in San Diego, and Chuck Overton, a 6-3 swing player from 
Salt Lake College in Salt Lake City.Nayab averaged 14 points and 12.1 assists 
last season; Overton averaged 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
 The high school player is John Williams (6-5) of Rialto High School. He 
averaged 15 points in his senior season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Leticia Oseguera, a 5-11 forward from Mater Dei, and Sabrina Roberson, a 5-8 
guard from Richard King High in Corpus Christi, Tex., have signed letters of 
intent to play basketball at UC Irvine, Anteater Coach Colleen Matsuhara 
announced. 
</P>
<P>
 Oseguera averaged 19 points and 10 rebounds and was the South Coast League's 
most valuable player last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Nichols, a diving standout at Laguna Hills High, has signed a letter of 
intent to attend Irvine, Anteater diving Coach Conni Pomeroy said. Nichols was 
a four-time Pacific Coast League diving champion and won two Southern Section 
diving titles. 
</P>
