ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: BURLINGTON AIR EXPRESS OKS PACT WITH COPENHAGEN FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Burlington Air Express said Monday that it has reached an agreement with Inter 
Express to allow the Copenhagen-based freight forwarder to use Burlington's 
name in shipments throughout Scandinavia. The new operations, based in 
Copenhagen, will include air, ocean and highway shipping services, warehousing 
and handling of high-value goods. Irvine-based Burlington Air Express, a 
$1-billion-a-year cargo handler with 490 offices worldwide, is a subsidiary of 
the Pittson Co., a Stamford, Conn., holding company. 
