<HEADLINE>
<P>
LAER PEARCE LEADS PUBLIC RELATIONS AWARD WINNERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANNE MICHAUD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Laer Pearce & Associates of Irvine led the list of winners at the 1994 Protos 
awards, which honor excellence among local public relations professionals. 
</P>
<P>
 Laer Pearce won seven first-place statues, followed closely by Paine & 
Associates of Costa Mesa, which won six.Four statues each were awarded to Amies 
Communications of Anaheim and Fullerton-based Beckman Instruments' in-house 
public relations team. 
</P>
<P>
 Nelson Communications Group of Irvine won two first-place statues. Winning one 
statue apiece were the in-house public relations duo at Odetics Inc. of 
Anaheim; Maples & Associates of Irvine; Gladstone International of Irvine; 
Morgan Marketing and Public Relations of Tustin; one-woman shop Teri Bruno; 
Roberts, Mealer & Co. of Santa Ana; Brighton Communications of Irvine; Fisher 
Business Communications of Santa Ana, Strategies of Costa Mesa and Orange-based 
Chapman University's in-house public relations department. 
</P>
<P>
 Linda Martin of Laer Pearce & Associates won the distinguished service award 
for an individual. 
</P>
<P>
 The award for distinguished service on the part of an organization went to The 
Times' Orange County edition. The newspaper was honored for its cash and 
advertising contributions to community events, as well as its 1993 Volunteers 
of Distinction awards program, said Cindy Beyl, a spokeswoman for The Times. 
</P>
<P>
 There were 190 entries in the competition, which is sponsored by the local 
chapter of the Public Relations Society of America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
