<HEADLINE>
<P>
FATAL STAMPEDE REPORTED IN MECCA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fatal stampede broke out before dawn Monday in Mecca during the "stoning the 
devil" ritual of the annual hajj pilgrimage, Saudi Arabian authorities 
reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of deaths was not given. A similar stampede in 1990 left 1,426 
people dead. 
</P>
<P>
 The official Saudi Press Agency, monitored in Bahrain, said 829 people have 
died in this year's hajj for a variety of reasons, including "deaths that 
resulted because of the heavy throngs throwing pebbles on Monday," but it gave 
no breakdown. 
</P>
<P>
 The ritual in the Muslim holy city involves pilgrims throwing pebbles at three 
boulders in a cavern. 
</P>
<P>
 Saudi officials previously said this year's hajj, which brought a record 2.5 
million pilgrims to Mecca, had been trouble-free. 
</P>
</TEXT>
