<TEXT>
<P>
 Rebel and government forces battled in Rwanda's capital Monday despite a 
promised cease-fire, blocking a U.N. envoy from reaching Kigali. 
</P>
<P>
 The day saw only intermittent signs of a 36-hour truce that both sides called 
to let U.N. envoy Iqbal Riza enter Kigali in an effort to halt seven weeks of 
carnage. 
</P>
