 At least five mortar bombs landed in the capital's U.N. compound, but there 
were no reports of injuries. Riza met leaders of the rebel Rwandan Patriotic 
Front north of Kigali and was to have traveled on to the capital for talks with 
the government side. 
</P>
<P>
 "Both sides seem to have difficulty in securing our security, so we cannot go 
along the route into Kigali," Riza said before heading back by road to Uganda. 
He said he hoped to fly to Kigali today. 
