REGIONAL ROUNDUP: GTE MAY RELOCATE 120 FROM THOUSAND OAKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GTE Corp. said that it will probably relocate about 120 employees from its 
regional headquarters in Thousand Oaks as part of a reorganization of some of 
its telephone operations support services. 
</P>
<P>
 Previously, the GTE California headquarters in Thousand Oaks handled billing, 
government affairs and public affairs for GTE telephone operations in 
California, Hawaii and the Northwest -- which includes Washington and Idaho. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the reorganization, each of the three regions will now be responsible 
for those support functions, and the 120 employees will be relocated to various 
locations. The three regions will continue to report to GTE Telephone 
Operations in Irving, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
 Stamford, Conn.-based GTE is the nation's largest independent local phone 
company. GTE California, its local subsidiary, will have about 2,400 employees 
remaining in Ventura County. 
