<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PAY-FONE SYSTEMS' PROFIT DOWN 24% IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pay-Fone Systems Inc., a Van Nuys-based automated payroll company, said its 
net income for the fiscal third quarter that ended March 31 was $105,574, down 
24% from $139,470 in the same quarter the previous year.Revenue for the fiscal 
third quarter also was down slightly to $1.27 million from $1.30 million in the 
same quarter last year. 
</P>
<P>
 For the nine months that ended March 31, net income was $167,440, down 17% 
from $200,735 the previous year. Revenue for the nine months was $3.37 million, 
down 3% from $3.49 million in the same period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the results to the cost of its acquisition of 
Concentric Computer Corp. of Aptos in January, and to the recession. 
</P>
</TEXT>
