<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; MAN FATALLY SHOT IN ROBBERY ATTEMPT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 41-year-old man was fatally shot early Monday by a gunman who walked up to 
his car and demanded money, a Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Eron Alonzo Mallagon of Palmdale was pronounced dead by paramedics at the 
scene of the 2:05 a.m. shooting, Deputy Irma Becerra said. 
</P>
<P>
 The shooting occurred shortly after Mallagon and a friend began driving home 
from El Charro bar. Mallagon stopped in the 38300 block of North 11th Street 
East when it appeared a motorist was following him. 
</P>
<P>
 A man with a gun got out of the other vehicle, opened Mallagon's door and 
demanded money, Becerra said. When Mallagon resisted, the gunman shot him, ran 
back to his car and fled, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 The passenger in Mallagon's car, whom authorities declined to identify for his 
safety, was uninjured, Becerra said. TIMOTHY WILLIAMS 
</P>
</TEXT>
