<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA CLARITA / ANTELOPE VALLEY; NEWHALL MAN STABBED WHILE ATTEMPTING TO 
PREVENT FIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK SABBATINI, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Newhall man was stabbed three times while trying to prevent a fight between 
two men Sunday night, authorities reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Gabriel Guerra, 34, was stabbed about 9:20 p.m. in a parking lot in the 24800 
block of Newhall Avenue, according to a report by Deputy Joe Skophammer of the 
Santa Clarita Valley sheriff's station.The assailant, believed to be in his 
early to mid-20s, remains at large. 
</P>
<P>
 A 10-year-old girl who witnessed the incident told deputies she saw Guerra 
step between two men who appeared as if they were going to fight. One of them 
stabbed Guerra and both fled the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 Guerra was "very uncooperative" with investigating deputies, stating he did 
not want to report the incident and did not want to press charges against his 
assailant, Skophammer said. Guerra told deputies that he did not know the two 
men and could not identify them if he saw them again. 
</P>
<P>
 He was taken to Henry Mayo Newhall Memorial Hospital in Valencia, where he was 
treated for three stab wounds just below the left side of his chest and other 
minor injuries, according to the report. Hospital officials said he remained at 
the hospital Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
