<TEXT>
<P>
 Oscar Saul -- Because of erroneous information provided to The Times, a story 
in Monday's editions incorrectly stated that screenwriter and author Oscar 
Saul, 81, had died Sunday in Cedars-Sinai Medical Center of prostate cancer. 
His son, Richard Saul, said Monday that the elder Saul is still living but is a 
patient at the hospital. The Times regrets the error. 
</P>
</TEXT>
